### 3.12 Signature & Acknowledgement

**Legal status banner (non-dismissable):**
Displayed before the signature area. States that the digital plan is a record of preferences only and is not legally binding under NZ law. Instructs the user to print, sign by hand, and have it witnessed by a health professional for clinical use.

**User must acknowledge all 4 statements before signing:**
1. This is a record of preferences to guide the healthcare team.
2. It will only be used when the user cannot make decisions for themselves.
3. Medically futile/inappropriate treatments will not be administered even if expressed.
4. The record may be held electronically and shared with other health care providers.

**Signature capture — two modes, toggled by the user:**
- **Draw mode** — HTML Canvas; mouse, touch, or stylus; crosshair cursor; retina-safe via `devicePixelRatio` scaling
- **Type mode** — text input renders the typed name onto the canvas in italic serif font, scaled to fit; saves as a PNG data URL identically to a drawn signature

Signature date: calendar date picker (auto-populated with today's date).

**Witness (Health Professional) — completed on the printed PDF:**
- Fields captured in-app for record only: First name(s), Last name, Designation, Email
- Date witnessed: calendar date picker
- Note explains that the witness section is completed on the printed PDF with a health professional present

**Completion prompt:** once all 4 acknowledgements are ticked and a signature is drawn/typed, a green banner appears with a direct "Export PDF" link.

---

### 3.13 PDF Export

**Export page features:**
- Plan completion summary with progress bar and clickable links to any incomplete sections
- Download PDF button — generates and triggers browser download
- Print button — generates PDF and opens browser print dialog via hidden iframe
- Save backup (.json) — exports plan as a JSON file for recovery
- "What to do next" checklist — 6 steps covering print, sign, witness, share, and review

**PDF generation (`pdf-lib`, client-side):**
- 4 pages mirroring the official form layout
- Red header bar with page number on every page; patient identity block top-right on pages 2–4 showing Surname, First Name/s, NHI Number, Date of Birth (each on its own line), and Phone/Mobile
- Noto Sans font (via `@fontsource/noto-sans`, served from `/public/fonts/`) for full Unicode support including Māori macron vowels (ā ē ī ō ū); `@pdf-lib/fontkit` required
- Helvetica (built-in) used for section headings to avoid OpenType ligature substitution issues (`fi`, `ll` etc.)
- Section headings auto-scale font size down if text is too wide for the heading band
- Address fields split on newline characters before rendering (pdf-lib ignores `\n` natively)
- Page 1: cover + personal information (Mobile first, Home Phone second)
- Page 2: EPA attorneys (grouped by type, with email), care contacts (with email), will, personal wishes
- Page 3: end-of-life preferences (checkboxes), body care, organ donation
- Page 4: treatment preferences table + signature block (actual signature image embedded via `embedPng`) + witness fields (with email)
- Signature date formatted as DD/MM/YYYY in the PDF

