### 3.14 Storage & Security

**Guest mode (no account) — current implementation:**
- All plans stored in `IndexedDB` (via `idb` library), keyed by UUID
- DB schema version 2 — supports multiple plans per device
- Data never leaves the device
- Warning displayed: data will be lost if browser storage is cleared
- JSON backup export/import available for recovery
- `clearAllData()` function available for settings page "Clear all data" and corrupt DB recovery

**Multi-plan IndexedDB schema:**

| Store | Key | Value |
|---|---|---|
| `plans` | UUID string | `{ id, plan, savedAt }` |
| `history` | Auto-increment int | `{ id, planId, plan, savedAt, version }` indexed by `planId` |

- Each save bumps the plan version and snapshots to history
- Last 5 versions retained per plan; older versions trimmed automatically
- `getAllFromIndex` calls have in-memory fallback filter in case index is unavailable during partial DB migration
- `dbPromise` resets on error so subsequent calls can retry
- `blocked`/`blocking` DB upgrade handlers prevent stale connections from blocking version migration
- Schema migration handles plans saved under older schema versions (single-EPA object → `attorneys` array; missing `email` fields)

**Authenticated mode (future):**
- Account creation via email + password or passkey (WebAuthn)
- Data stored server-side, encrypted at rest (AES-256)
- HTTPS enforced; all API traffic TLS 1.3+
- Session management via secure, `HttpOnly` cookies

---

### 3.15 Updates & Versioning
- Users can edit any section at any time
- Each save creates a timestamped version history (last 5 versions retained per plan)
- Per-plan home screen shows date last updated
- Auto-save debounced at 1.5 seconds after any field change (PlanContext level)
- Field-level saves on Care Contacts and Treatment Preferences use a separate 600ms debounce to prevent focus loss during tab navigation

---

### 3.16 Section Navigation
Every section page has a four-item top navigation bar:

```
← Previous  |  Saving… / All saved  |  ⌂ Home  |  Next →
```

- **← Previous** — navigates to the preceding section (absent on Personal Information, the first section)
- **Save status** — shows "Saving…", "Unsaved changes", or "All saved"
- **⌂ Home** — navigates to the plan selector (`/`)
- **Next →** — navigates directly to the next section without requiring a save action

A sticky **"Save & Continue"** button in the bottom bar also advances to the next section and explicitly saves first.

