### 3.17 Contacts Integration

**Applies to:** Section 3.4 (EPA) and Section 3.5 (Care Decision contacts)

#### Behaviour
- Each contact entry surfaces an **"Import from Contacts"** button alongside the manual fields
- Uses the browser-native Contact Picker API (`navigator.contacts.select()`)
- On selection, fields are auto-mapped:

| Contacts field | Form field |
|---|---|
| Given name | First name(s) |
| Family name | Last name |
| Address | Address (EPA only) |
| Phone labelled "mobile" | Mobile |
| Phone labelled "home" | Home phone |
| Phone labelled "work" | Daytime phone (EPA only) |
| First phone if no label match | Primary phone field |

- All imported values are editable after import — contact is copied, not linked
- Relationship and email fields are never auto-filled; must be entered manually

#### Browser Support & Fallback
- Contact Picker API supported on: Chrome for Android 80+, Safari iOS 16+
- On unsupported browsers: button is hidden; manual entry only
- Feature detection via `'contacts' in navigator && 'ContactsManager' in window`

#### Privacy
- Browser prompts for permission each time the picker is opened — no persistent access
- No contact data stored beyond what the user explicitly imports

#### Edge Cases
- Contact with no phone: import name/address only; phone fields left blank
- Contact with 3+ phones: inline disambiguation UI to assign numbers to correct fields
- Contact with no address (EPA): address fields left blank for manual entry

---

### 3.18 Date Pickers
All date fields use a consistent NZ-format calendar picker:

**Personal Information — Date of Birth:**
- Month dropdown (Jan–Dec) and year dropdown (1900 to current year) for quick navigation
- Day grid (Su–Sa) with correct first-day-of-week alignment
- Selected date highlighted in red; today outlined in red
- Stores as ISO `YYYY-MM-DD`; displays as `DD/MM/YYYY`
- Default view opens at current year minus 30 (practical for date of birth)
- Keyboard accessible: Enter/Space opens and selects, Escape closes, calendar has `role="dialog"`

**Signature — Signature Date and Date Witnessed:**
- Same calendar UI without year dropdown (dates are near present)
- "Today" shortcut button
- Auto-populated with today's date on first open

---

### 3.19 Auto-Resizing Text Fields
All multi-line text fields (textareas) across the app automatically grow to fit their content:

- `resize: none` — manual drag handle removed; height is managed programmatically
- `overflow: hidden` — prevents scrollbar flash during resize
- `ref` callback resizes the element immediately on mount — existing saved content is shown in full when a page loads
- `onInput` handler resizes on every keystroke as the user types
- After `reset()` populates form fields from saved data, a `requestAnimationFrame` callback resizes all textareas on the page
- RHF `register()` ref is merged with the resize ref so both operate correctly on the same element

Applies to: address fields (Personal Info, EPA), personal wishes (3 fields), funeral wishes, organ donation comments, treatment preferences (both columns), end-of-life at-home address.

---

### 3.20 Keyboard & Tab Navigation
All form pages are fully keyboard-navigable:

- Tab moves through fields in logical DOM order
- Form-level `onBlur` is avoided on pages with `useFieldArray` (Care Contacts, Treatment Preferences) — it caused `reset()` to fire mid-tab, destroying focus. These pages use per-field `onBlur` with a debounced save instead
- `useEffect` reset only runs once on initial mount (via `initialised` ref) to prevent re-renders destroying focus during a session
- Date picker: Enter/Space opens, Escape closes at both trigger and popover level
- Date picker day buttons are tabbable within the open popover

---

### 3.21 Local Network Access (Development)
To serve the app to other devices on the local network during development:

- Next.js dev server started with `--hostname 0.0.0.0` to bind all interfaces
- `allowedDevOrigins` configured in `next.config.ts` with the local subnet (e.g. `"192.168.*.*"`)
- Devices access via `http://` (not `https://`) — e.g. `http://192.168.x.x:3000`
- If a browser auto-upgrades to HTTPS, clear the HSTS entry via `chrome://net-internals/#hsts`

---

### 3.22 Responsive Design & Accessibility
- Fully responsive: optimised for desktop (1024px+), tablet (768px), and mobile (375px+)
- Large tap targets (minimum 44×44px) for older users on mobile
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance: keyboard navigable, sufficient colour contrast, screen reader support
- `<label>` elements correctly associated with all inputs
- Progress indicator showing completion status across all form sections
- Auto-save indicator in top navigation bar on every section page
- Hydration guards on all client-only components prevent server/client mismatch errors when accessed from other devices on the network

